{
  "stem": "9168.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know that they wanted me to-- wanted it to be in the Senate, but nobody was retiring.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The last man who retired there was 84.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was working in my Denver court down here, the District Court, with Judge Robert T.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Kingsley, when the call came at the end of May, 1972 from the Speaker's office to my court.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Speaker Carl Albert of Oklahoma, whom I did not know, and asking to speak to me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my judge immediately-- he knew what was in the works eventually-- called a recess.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went, and he asked me if I could be in Washington, DC the next day to be sworn in as a reporter of debates.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I could return to Denver and finish a period of two weeks' notice, which is what I did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then it was in '72 that I-- in June 19th, right around Watergate time, that I went to Washington, DC to report as an official reporter of debates on the team there in the United States House of Representatives.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While I was-- I did not receive an award in Congress, Gary, but I was a court reporter-- and I think this is very important-- in 1978.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I was a reporter of debates in 1978, when President Jimmy Carter established the President's Commission on the Holocaust, appointing Elie Wiesel as chairman.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was invited to the special ceremony in the rotunda, because I was the only court-- court reporter at Nuremberg who was part of the Congress, to this wonderful, special ceremony with Elie Wiesel, telling his story with his eight-year-old boy there then.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was a great honor for me to be able to go to that.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
